      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load are the primary mechanical QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and are directly linked to the device performance claims submitted to FDA. These QoIs are clinically relevant surrogates for in vivo fixation stability."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk level 3.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities directly replicate the ASTM F1717 test protocol that constitutes the intended use of the model. The non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw geometry evaluated in validation matches the device configuration for which the model is applied in clinical research and regulatory support contexts."
