    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for model risk level 3. The single deficiency in Test conditions (achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is acknowledged; the assessment team determined that the breadth of ensemble agreement across two laboratories and the direct correspondence to the ASTM F1717 protocol provide sufficient overall confidence to accept the model for its intended application. Acceptance is conditional on re-evaluation if the model is extended to loading configurations beyond the single compression-bending condition validated here.",
